									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I enjoyed this piece, which is essentially a description of a person. I especially think that the language in the second paragraph is great. Very tight and precise, almost (in a good way) list like. Also, it&#8217;s both detailed and revealing about the character. </p>
<p>I have some small nits:<br />
&gt; where is hung<br />
Should be, &#8220;where it hung&#8221;</p>
<p>&gt; he could get into trouble if he felt without a final check of his<br />
&gt; appearance<br />
It seems that &#8220;felt&#8221; is the wrong verb here, unless I&#8217;m misreading the sentence.</p>
<p>&gt; He had had his hair cut but no one would see under his cap but he<br />
&gt; would know.<br />
I think that this sentence reads a bit clumsily. I think it&#8217;s the two uses of &#8220;but&#8221; in the same sentence.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

